# Purpose

Enforce frontend-specific coding conventions. Universal TypeScript rules are in `global/coding-standards.mdc`.

# Rules

## Naming

- React component files: `PascalCase.tsx` â€” file name matches the exported component (e.g. `Button.tsx` exports `const Button`).
- Component prop type files: `<Component>.types.ts` (e.g. `Button.types.ts`).
- Co-located test files: `<Component>.test.tsx` (e.g. `Button.test.tsx`).
- Zustand slice files: `<name>.state.ts`, `<name>.types.ts`, `index.ts` (e.g. `user.state.ts`).
- All other non-component TypeScript files: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g. `rest.ts`, `build-url.ts`).

## Imports

- Path alias: `@/` maps to `src/` (configured in `tsconfig.json` and `vite.config.ts`).
- Use `@/` for all imports that cross directory boundaries (e.g. `import api from '@/api'`).
- DO NOT use relative `../../` imports when `@/` resolves the target.

## Types

- API payload types (`AccessToken`, `LoginUserInput`, `RegisterUserInput`, etc.) are generated by Orval. Import from `@/_types/_gen`.
- DO NOT manually define or duplicate generated API types.
- Regenerate after OpenAPI spec changes: `npm run generate-types` inside `frontend/`.
- Use Zod for client-side runtime validation (e.g. validating JWT payload shape with `jwtPayloadSchema.safeParse`).

## Error Handling

- Catch `CustomError` from `@/services/error` for structured API errors.
- Access `error.issues` for field-level validation messages from the backend.
- Always log errors with `logging.error(error)` from `@/services/logging`.
- DO NOT swallow errors silently.
- Set `isLoading: false` in a `finally` block, not in both the success and error paths.

```typescript
// âś… Correct pattern
try {
    setState(prev => ({ ...prev, isLoading: true }));
    const response = await api.service.resources.authentication.login(payload);
    // handle success
} catch (error) {
    if (error instanceof CustomError) {
        // error.issues contains structured backend validation errors
    }
    logging.error(error as Error);
} finally {
    setState(prev => ({ ...prev, isLoading: false }));
}
```

# Anti-Patterns

- DO NOT name component files `kebab-case.tsx` â€” use `PascalCase.tsx`.
- DO NOT define API payload types manually â€” use generated `@/_types/_gen` types.
- DO NOT use relative `../../` imports â€” use `@/` alias.
- DO NOT swallow errors silently.

# Checklist

- [ ] Component files named `PascalCase.tsx`
- [ ] Prop types in co-located `<Component>.types.ts`
- [ ] No manual API type definitions â€” `@/_types/_gen` used
- [ ] `@/` alias used instead of `../../`
- [ ] Errors caught and logged, not swallowed
